gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 118, Pistons 112
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Pistons, 118-112. Jalen Brunson led the Knicks with 42 points (13-24 FG, 7-12 3PT), eight assists, and six rebounds as Julius Randle totaled 29 points, 10 rebounds, and eight assists. Cade Cunningham led Detroit with 31 points and eight assists while Killian Hayes added 23 points. The Knicks improve to 11-7 as the Pistons move to 2-17.
